Yesterday was Uryu's birthday,

72
00:04:47,374 --> 00:04:50,374
so we all got together to celebrate it.

73
00:04:50,374 --> 00:04:54,174
He had a terrible birthday last year.

74
00:04:54,174 --> 00:04:56,474
A terrible birthday?

75
00:04:56,474 --> 00:05:00,674
We got together last year at about the same time,

76
00:05:00,674 --> 00:05:02,774
and since it was Uryu's birthday,

77
00:05:02,774 --> 00:05:06,374
Ishiguri said that we should surprise him.

78
00:05:06,374 --> 00:05:10,474
We snuck into the room Uryu was sleeping in through the veranda

79
00:05:10,474 --> 00:05:13,974
and popped some party crackers near his ear.

80
00:05:13,974 --> 00:05:18,374
Then he got panic and started crying.

81
00:05:18,374 --> 00:05:20,974
On top of that, a video of his plight was taken

82
00:05:20,974 --> 00:05:23,074
and it was uploaded on the web by Ishiguri.

83
00:05:23,074 --> 00:05:24,474
I see.

84
00:05:24,474 --> 00:05:26,274
As to you three,

85
00:05:26,274 --> 00:05:30,374
it seems that you all have more than enough motive to kill Mr. Ishiguri.

86
00:05:30,374 --> 00:05:31,874
Motive?

87
00:05:31,874 --> 00:05:35,274
The only time I went to Ishiguri's room was just that once.

88
00:05:35,274 --> 00:05:38,674
Other than that, I was with all of you the whole time, wasn't I?

89
00:05:38,674 --> 00:05:41,474
I was with you while the detective was talking.

90
00:05:41,474 --> 00:05:43,874
"The air conditioner in this room isn't working well,

91
00:05:43,874 --> 00:05:46,574
so go to Ishiguri's room and rest."

92
00:05:46,574 --> 00:05:49,074
Wasn't it me who told that to the kid?

93
00:05:49,074 --> 00:05:51,274
-Is that true? -Yes.

94
00:05:51,274 --> 00:05:53,974
After that, I saw Mr. Ishiguri in the corridor,

95
00:05:53,974 --> 00:05:55,774
so I had him take me with him.

96
00:05:55,774 --> 00:05:57,674
How could I possibly commit murder

97
00:05:57,674 --> 00:05:59,674
knowing that a child is sleeping in the room?

98
00:05:59,674 --> 00:06:01,174
True.

99
00:06:03,374 --> 00:06:05,874
No matter what kind of trick was used,

100
00:06:05,874 --> 00:06:08,174
I thought it was only possible for a man

101
00:06:08,174 --> 00:06:09,674
to move the heavy corpse of Mr. Ishiguri,

102
00:06:09,674 --> 00:06:12,874
which was none other than the only male suspect, Mr. Takanashi.

103
00:06:12,874 --> 00:06:14,574
-Yes. -But...

104
00:06:14,574 --> 00:06:16,274
if it was only to lift the top part of the body,

105
00:06:16,274 --> 00:06:18,474
wouldn't a woman be able to do it too?

106
00:06:18,474 --> 00:06:20,774
One could place the corpse up against the doorway

107
00:06:20,774 --> 00:06:22,974
and let go of the body so it would slide down,

108
00:06:22,974 --> 00:06:24,574
then finally close the door.

109
00:06:24,574 --> 00:06:27,374
No. I think that would be impossible

110
00:06:27,374 --> 00:06:29,374
because the buttocks of the corpse

111
00:06:29,374 --> 00:06:31,074
was in a position that blocked the door.

112
00:06:31,074 --> 00:06:33,874
Besides, the spare key to Mr. Ishiguri's room

113
00:06:33,874 --> 00:06:35,974
hasn't been found yet either.

114
00:06:35,974 --> 00:06:38,074
What's the key like?

115
00:06:38,074 --> 00:06:40,374
It seems to have been the same kind

116
00:06:40,374 --> 00:06:42,974
as the one found in the pocket of the corpse.

117
00:06:42,974 --> 00:06:45,774
We haven't heard that it's been found yet.

118
00:06:45,774 --> 00:06:48,374
Then, maybe it was disposed together with the trash?

119
00:06:48,374 --> 00:06:52,274
I helped throw the trash away together with Ran.

120
00:06:52,274 --> 00:06:53,474
What?

121
00:06:53,474 --> 00:06:57,374
We put it into the trunk of Mr. Takanashi's car, though.

122
00:06:57,374 --> 00:07:00,274
We were told that he would take it home and throw it away.

123
00:07:00,274 --> 00:07:04,274
Then, maybe the key is in that trash.

124
00:07:04,274 --> 00:07:05,674
Check it immediately!

125
00:07:05,674 --> 00:07:07,474
-Yes, sir! -Yes, sir!

126
00:07:07,474 --> 00:07:11,574
Did anyone else ask you to do anything else?

127
00:07:11,574 --> 00:07:14,374
Ms. Kotone asked us to put the sports drink

128
00:07:14,374 --> 00:07:16,674
back into the freezer.

129
00:07:16,674 --> 00:07:17,974
So we did that.

130
00:07:17,974 --> 00:07:20,374
Put the sports drink into the freezer?

131
00:07:20,374 --> 00:07:23,074
She said that she likes to drink it frozen.

132
00:07:23,074 --> 00:07:25,774
At the time, there was a fuss

133
00:07:25,774 --> 00:07:26,974
about Mr. Ishiguri not coming out of his room.

134
00:07:26,974 --> 00:07:30,574
Ms. Kotone was holding a PET bottle.

135
00:07:30,574 --> 00:07:33,774
I think she wanted to freeze it again because it was starting to melt.

136
00:07:33,774 --> 00:07:36,274
She just made it look like that and put the key in there.

137
00:07:36,274 --> 00:07:39,074
A key wouldn't fit inside.

138
00:07:39,074 --> 00:07:44,874
After I took a shower, I took a sip of that drink,

139
00:07:44,874 --> 00:07:46,774
but it was totally frozen.

140
00:07:46,774 --> 00:07:48,674
Oh, that's right.

141
00:07:48,674 --> 00:07:51,174
Ms. Machi told us that she would re-wrap

142
00:07:51,174 --> 00:07:53,674
the grip tapes of our rackets.

143
00:07:53,674 --> 00:07:55,674
We left our rackets with her.

144
00:07:55,674 --> 00:07:57,374
And while she was at it, she also changed

145
00:07:57,374 --> 00:08:00,374
the strings of our rackets, too.

146
00:08:01,474 --> 00:08:03,374
Inspector Yokomizo.

147
00:08:03,374 --> 00:08:06,774
We found no key in the trash.

148
00:08:06,774 --> 00:08:07,874
I see.

149
00:08:07,874 --> 00:08:10,874
The sports drink in the freezer is frozen solid

150
00:08:10,874 --> 00:08:15,474
and it doesn't seem possible for a key to be inside it.

151
00:08:15,474 --> 00:08:17,574
What about the rackets?

152
00:08:17,574 --> 00:08:20,474
We checked the rackets of everyone,

153
00:08:20,474 --> 00:08:22,874
but there wasn't anything that looks like a key attached anywhere.

154
00:08:22,874 --> 00:08:24,574
Speaking of rackets, we got a report

155
00:08:24,574 --> 00:08:27,274
that the strings of the racket under the corpse's buttocks

156
00:08:27,274 --> 00:08:29,774
seem to be out of shape in several spots.

157
00:08:29,774 --> 00:08:32,474
The strings? Why?

158
00:08:32,474 --> 00:08:33,574
We don't know.

159
00:08:33,574 --> 00:08:37,474
Also, the shape of the copper vase that had blood on it,

160
00:08:37,474 --> 00:08:40,674
matched the wound on the head of the corpse.

161
00:08:40,674 --> 00:08:44,074
But for some reason, it seems there was water in the vase.

162
00:08:44,074 --> 00:08:45,474
Water?

163
00:08:45,474 --> 00:08:47,774
Why would water be inside the murder weapon?

164
00:08:47,774 --> 00:08:50,274
By the way, the estimated time of death

165
00:08:50,274 --> 00:08:53,474
was two to three hours before the corpse was found.

166
00:08:53,474 --> 00:08:56,274
Depending on the temperature of the room at that time,

167
00:08:56,274 --> 00:08:59,874
there may be a discrepancy of about 30 minutes or so.

168
00:08:59,874 --> 00:09:02,974
I had lunch with everyone here

169
00:09:02,974 --> 00:09:06,074
around three hours before the corpse was found.

170
00:09:06,074 --> 00:09:10,774
All three of them had the chance to commit the crime.

171
00:09:10,774 --> 00:09:14,174
You. Didn't you see the culprit?

172
00:09:14,174 --> 00:09:16,274
You were in the room the whole time, weren't you?

173
00:09:16,274 --> 00:09:18,374
I was fast asleep.

174
00:09:18,374 --> 00:09:22,174
So you also don't remember that Sonoko and I

175
00:09:22,174 --> 00:09:24,274
took the cold Chinese noodles to that room, do you?

176
00:09:24,274 --> 00:09:26,574
Nope. I think I was asleep.

177
00:09:26,574 --> 00:09:28,774
Come to think of it, Ran.

178
00:09:28,774 --> 00:09:32,474
Back then, you said something weird, didn't you?

179
00:09:32,474 --> 00:09:35,174
It seems he's asleep, so why not let him be?

180
00:09:35,174 --> 00:09:37,674
Missing lunch won't kill him either.

181
00:09:37,674 --> 00:09:38,974
That's true.

182
00:09:38,974 --> 00:09:42,674
It seems that the air conditioner of this room is working, too.

183
00:09:42,674 --> 00:09:44,974
How would you know that

184
00:09:44,974 --> 00:09:46,774
despite being outside of the room?

185
00:09:46,774 --> 00:09:50,474
That's because my toes were cold.

186
00:09:50,474 --> 00:09:52,674
I'm sure that cold air was leaking out

187
00:09:52,674 --> 00:09:54,974
through the space under the door.

188
00:09:54,974 --> 00:09:58,274
If I remember correctly, Ms. Machi said something similar.

189
00:09:58,274 --> 00:10:00,174
I think he was in the room.

190
00:10:00,174 --> 00:10:02,374
It seems like the air conditioner was running.

191
00:10:03,574 --> 00:10:07,474
I see. That's how it is.

192
00:10:07,474 --> 00:10:11,174
The culprit ingeniously used an object that doesn't keep its form

193
00:10:11,174 --> 00:10:15,174
and completed the locked room murder.

194
00:10:18,412 --> 00:10:19,912
Officer.

195
00:10:20,052 --> 00:10:22,152
Maybe it was an accident after all?

196
00:10:22,152 --> 00:10:26,852
Ishiguri's corpse was on the floor and was blocking the door.

197
00:10:26,852 --> 00:10:29,752
If there was a racket under his buttocks,

198
00:10:29,752 --> 00:10:32,952
maybe when he tried to pick up the racket,

199
00:10:32,952 --> 00:10:36,852
the vase just happened to fall on him?

200
00:10:36,852 --> 00:10:39,752
On top of that, the room was locked.

201
00:10:39,752 --> 00:10:42,752
The spare key hasn't been found yet, has it?

202
00:10:42,752 --> 00:10:44,252
No.

203
00:10:44,252 --> 00:10:47,552
The area around the villa is being checked now.

204
00:10:47,552 --> 00:10:48,952
However, we've still got no such report.

205
00:10:48,952 --> 00:10:50,552
I don't care what it is,

206
00:10:50,552 --> 00:10:52,352
but this is what I call messy handwriting.

207
00:10:52,352 --> 00:10:54,452
As long as I can read it, it's fine.

208
00:10:54,452 --> 00:10:56,852
Okay, he sat down.

209
00:10:56,852 --> 00:11:00,752
Like usual, I'll fire the tranquilizer gun at Pops.

210
00:11:02,152 --> 00:11:04,852
What are you doing, Conan?

211
00:11:04,852 --> 00:11:08,252
The lid of my wristwatch broke.

212
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:11,552
Even if I wanted to, I guess I can't start

213
00:11:11,552 --> 00:11:14,052
the Sleeping Kogoro stunt in front of him.

214
00:11:14,052 --> 00:11:17,852
He's Bourbon, a member of the Black Organization.

215
00:11:17,852 --> 00:11:19,852
I can't afford to have him find out that I'm Shinichi Kudo,

216
00:11:19,852 --> 00:11:21,852
whose body has become a child's because of the organization's drug.

217
00:11:21,852 --> 00:11:24,852
Even if Vermouth says nothing about it,

218
00:11:24,852 --> 00:11:28,052
they may still find out that the same thing's happened to Ai, too.

219
00:11:28,052 --> 00:11:30,452
Besides,

220
00:11:30,452 --> 00:11:33,052
maybe the sound that we heard when we were downstairs

221
00:11:33,052 --> 00:11:35,852
wasn't the sound of the vase falling, was it?

222
00:11:35,852 --> 00:11:37,752
Back then, only the corpse

223
00:11:37,752 --> 00:11:40,452
and the sleeping boy were in that room.

224
00:11:40,452 --> 00:11:43,352
Besides, the vase wouldn't fall on its own.

225
00:11:43,352 --> 00:11:47,352
I guess it was the sound of the house creaking after all.

226
00:11:47,352 --> 00:11:48,752
If it was the creaking of the house,

227
00:11:48,752 --> 00:11:51,452
I also heard it when we were eating cold Chinese noodles.

228
00:11:51,452 --> 00:11:53,052
It was totally different.

229
00:11:53,052 --> 00:11:54,652
Hey, hey.

230
00:11:54,652 --> 00:11:57,152
Speaking of cold Chinese noodles,

231
00:11:57,152 --> 00:11:58,852
you use ice when making it, right?

232
00:11:58,852 --> 00:12:01,952
Yes. The noodles that are boiled

233
00:12:01,952 --> 00:12:03,952
are cooled down in ice water.

234
00:12:03,952 --> 00:12:07,252
Hey, cut out the unnecessary talk.

235
00:12:07,252 --> 00:12:12,452
But ice melts, doesn't it?

236
00:12:12,452 --> 00:12:14,352
That's common sense!

237
00:12:14,352 --> 00:12:17,652
If so, if the vase was made of ice,

238
00:12:17,652 --> 00:12:20,752
it would eventually melt and fall on its own.

239
00:12:20,752 --> 00:12:22,052
You idiot.

240
00:12:22,052 --> 00:12:24,052
That vase is made of bronze.

241
00:12:24,052 --> 00:12:26,652
I mean, you touched it too, didn't you?

242
00:12:26,652 --> 00:12:29,152
Please wait.

243
00:12:29,152 --> 00:12:32,552
If a lot of ice is stacked

244
00:12:32,552 --> 00:12:34,652
only on one side in the vase,

245
00:12:34,652 --> 00:12:38,252
and it was placed near the rim of the shelf,

246
00:12:38,252 --> 00:12:40,252
it's just a matter of time before the ice would melt,

247
00:12:40,252 --> 00:12:43,552
and the vase would tilt out of balance and fall on its own, right?

248
00:12:43,552 --> 00:12:47,252
But if a large amount of ice were to be carried around,

249
00:12:47,252 --> 00:12:49,252
wouldn't anyone have noticed it?

250
00:12:49,252 --> 00:12:53,452
No, you can do so without holding it in your hands.

251
00:12:53,452 --> 00:12:55,452
When the Chinese noodles were being made,

252
00:12:55,452 --> 00:12:58,652
all three of them were in their tennis wear.

253
00:12:58,652 --> 00:13:02,652
The pants of men's tennis wear have large pockets

254
00:13:02,652 --> 00:13:05,552
so that tennis balls would fit into them.

255
00:13:05,552 --> 00:13:08,852
There are also skirts in women's tennis wear

256
00:13:08,852 --> 00:13:10,852
with pockets big enough for the balls to fit in.

